text: #measureformeasure @donmarwarehouse is extraordinary. so cleverly done, the play is performed twice, once in a traditional setting (1604) and once in the climate of today. despite obvious differences, or updates, to be more accurate, the two are strikingly similar, scarily so, showing once more how little the world has advanced in 400 years. the production is particularly impactful in light of the recent #metoo campaign. with compelling performances from a strong cast, and disturbingly resounding relevance to the world around us, this is theatre at its most powerful.

text:
to anyone who needs to hear this:
your abuse was still abuse even if they didnâ€™t hit you. 
any penetration or oral sex without consent is rape. 
healing has no timeline. 
there will be people who will stand by your abuser. those people do not deserve to be in your life. 
our brains remember/forget parts of traumatic events in order to survive. what ever you remember/forget is valid. 
donâ€™t listen to the strangers on the internet who spew hate about your experiences. 
the world is cruel to survivors but darling i will always believe you. 
no matter what anyone says: it was not your fault. 
it was not your fault. 
it was not your fault. 
i see you. 
i hear you. 
i believe you.

text:
me too!!! i have chosen this bright, cheerful photo in hopes it will get attention for this may be my most important post to date for it deals with what so many of us are bringing to light - sexual violence. i have been trying to have a relationship with a man after years of shying away from having one. as usual, as soon as i get involved, dreams, triggers, innocent actions all pull up long buried memories. i feel like when i am not pursuing a relationship i forget things that have happened to me when in so-called relationships. iâ€™m sure suppressing these memories feed my depression and anxiety but, until lately, it hasnâ€™t occurred to me that these would be the cause. i rather blamed myself, seeing what happened as the effect of me being damaged. i victim shamed myself. i have never even spoken to anyone about this. i know that not only women have had violence and/or emotional abuse perpetrated upon them, and that not only i have experienced it numerous times. i also know that empowering myself by horseback riding, traveling solo, and taking charge of my friendships with men are my armor and my defense mechanism. to give any thought to these past occurrences sends me into a panic attack. but today, realizing i canâ€™t even watch a romantic movie without a visceral reaction i know i must somehow process what has happened to me. please, if you are grappling with anything that sounds similar, take a look at even seemingly small things that, at the time, you may not have seen as assault or rape and reconsider what you felt and if it did damage that you stuffed deep down. get it out in the light and talk to someone. staying a victim, even if only in your sub conscious mind, is the most damaging way to live. you deserve better!
 #live #depressionrecovery #horsetherapy #friendsarethebest #therapy #horsesaremylife #liveauthentic #rescuedog #remembertobreathe #horsesofinstagram #laughteristhebestmedicine #healyourlife #iamworthit #anxietywarrior #mentalhealth #mentalillnessawareness #todayisagoodday #youcanhealyourlife #suicideprevention #recovering #therapydog #horselover #happy #smile #ireland #femaleempowerment #sexualassault #highlysensitiveperson #introvert #metoo

text:
â€œi was so afraid to take your self-defense class i almost didnâ€™t come. iâ€™ve had bad experiences that make me afraid to even hear about violence, but now i feel so empowered and confident. thank you, lori. youâ€™ve given me the tools i needed to face my fears and become powerful!â€
.
.
.
.this right here! this is why i teach. growing up, i experienced sexual assault many times, starting at a young age, so i know what it feels like to be scared and fearful of it happening again. so many girls and women carry pain from molestation and sexual abuse and they donâ€™t even know why theyâ€™re fearful, and that unawareness makes them easy targets for people who want to hurt them. they avoid learning self defense because it makes them come face to face with their past, which causes a natural stress reaction in their bodies and usually sends them into survival mode. in my classes and workshops, i talk openly about real threats and perpetrators and dangerous people, but i teach from a place of healing and positivity and empowerment with a sensitivity to survivors. even though iâ€™ve had awful things happen to me, i also know about overcoming those traumas and gaining freedom from triggers and the past, and iâ€™ll be passing on those skills and truths until every girl and woman is safe and empowered. iâ€™ve looked evil in the eye and faced my demons. they donâ€™t scare me anymore. and now iâ€™m helping others to do the same. you donâ€™t have to live in fear. you can move from #survivor to #overcomer! letâ€™s take the #metoo movement into healing movement, taking back what the enemy thought he stole. #strongertogether . photo cred:@derrick_corcuera .
.

text:
standing firm sometimes means standing alone. i learned this while i dug my heels in and said enough is enough is enough. i will not sit idly by in the face of wrongdoing and i will not be ok with something that is simply not ok. in this particular setting, my situation was (surprisingly?) not taken seriously. but it did not silence me. it made my voice grow louder. i felt like a lion in the presence of sheep. i took a risk that had me feeling temporarily disappointed but overall empowered. outside of that situation i learned who is supportive and in what ways. 
all of this fueled the fire that lives within me. my fire shines a light on that which is to be seen and acts like a burn to that which requires it. 
this is my most recent #metoo story. â€¢
â€¢
#metoomovement #empoweredwomenempowerwomen #storyteller #useyourvoice #honoryourtruth

text:
i began eating modified #keto (think passover without the matzah or sugar) last may (2018). the photo on the left (photo credit: pamela kanda) was from a year ago (november 2017). photo on the right was a week ago. 
i haven't weighed myself since september, just before our bathroom construction began, but between may-september, i'd released 30 lbs. i can't see it when i look in the mirror, but i see it in these photos.

my #weight gain began in my 20s. while it seemed everyone else was exploring life as an adult, i was shutting down, in and out of the hospital with suicide attempts, severe #depression, and #ptsd that was rearing its head now that i was physically in a safe place. 
my weight was a way to keep others at arm's length, especially men and male attention. it was also a way to be #big (physically) in the world without having to be big (emotionally, spiritually) in the world. it was my #protection. it was one of the ways i #survived. 
now, between #trauma therapy, coaching, #trusting myself, embracing my gifts, and acknowledging that for decades, i hid and lived a lie so others wouldn't feel uncomfortable with the truth, i no longer need to hide behind the weight. i can be in the world, and i can be big without needing to be physically #big. #metoo

text:
this is what work from home looks like!
.
don't miss out the fact that i'm handling the phone too ğŸ’
.
i always wonder how work  from home moms really manage doing the household work, taking care of the baby, cooking, taking naps, thinking about their own careers..and what not.
.
i work 9-6 so it's pretty easy some days to concentrate just on work. but how is it managed at home when distraction is just a synonym of our #existence itself. for some reasons, i feel that women would be better managers if and when the workload is shared equally. and by workload i mean sharing these responsibilities.ğŸ‘‡ğŸ»
.
1. #house - getting groceries, fixing maids (it's tough), getting broken things repaired.
.
2. #baby - feed them, cook for them, think about what to cook for them, arrange their room and toys, think about what activities to do with them.
.
3. #office - fight the mindset of same work - same salary ?? same work - same extra hours?? same work - similar growth??
.
4. #relationship - with the spouse, with the baby..with friends and family. is there the same amount of effort put in, in maintaining these relatonships?
.
5. #mind matters- hands down, even to plan what to cook for next 1 week is draining and mentally exhausting.. and then there's plethora of things that need to thought through on an everyday basis.
.
6. the #metoo situation - office, work, roads.. imagine a constant state of mind where u think that you can be #judged or #touched anytime, thinking about whom to stare back, whom to ignore, how to kick out abusive people from your life.
.
now when all these things are taken care of by both partners, that is when one can start talking about equality both at work and home.
.
i started writing this post because i was in awe of the way so many women manage everything, but i got off the topic and, here i am now, not knowing how i really got here. ğŸ¤·
.
either way, this post is meant for all those people (all genders) raised in partiarchal mindset who still refuse to come out of their comfort zone..
who still refuse to challenge the existing norms, bcz hey, who's wants to be the black sheep..
.
#equality #workfromhome #respect

text:
story time: #metoo .
this time last year i drop kicked a dude.
.
my friend @kittenkuroi & i were on tour & decided to see her friends show in san fran. waiting for her friend to get there we were standing at the curb. dude walks by & grabs my butt. .
in heeled boots, i pivoted & kicked him square in the butt. kitten pulled me back & said, â€œwhat did you do?!â€ i didnâ€™t know.
.
her friend rolled up, we were escorted to vip. after the show head security walked us out & said, â€œwhen we saw you sparta kick that dude we were all ready to back you.â€ my first thought was to be embarrassed over my accidental reaction.
.
for days we were both saying wow! that actually happened.
.
iâ€™ve taken a few krav classes & a self defense class. i donâ€™t know if i need to go around kicking people. but, having come from a violent environment i was stoked that i responded rather than shutting down & taking the assault.
.
let us continue...
.
just this month i was aggressively solicited by a major network producer for 5k for one night, & by a photographer for the same amount to indulge him in his fetish. ğŸ‘¿ğŸ¤¬hard pass. i donâ€™t even want to know what the hell that is. i donâ€™t know if thatâ€™s the going rate & i donâ€™t care. .
.
itâ€™s not #metoo if you take the job. you walk away, thatâ€™s what you do. it doesnâ€™t matter if you need the money. if you decide that youâ€™re okay with that - do what you do -  donâ€™t come back & call him names & blame him for this â€œviolation of you as woman.â€
.
youâ€™re better than that. youâ€™re worth more than that. stand the hell up for yourself. hold people accountable for their behavior. .
.
this morning i let a photographer have it. â€œi saw bikini pics & 2+2...â€ no sir, thatâ€™s 0-100 thatâ€™s a major leap. iâ€™m a woman not a piece of a$$. my value is so much more than that. .
.
iâ€™ve been physically assaulted by trainers, cornered & yelled at & called a b*tch while management & security did nothing. .â€
.
.
iâ€™m not a victim. being a victim is a mindset. you choose who you are going to be. you do. and you do it one choice at a time. decide who you want to be and make sure your choices line up accordingly.

text:
women. there was a time when i was afraid of women. i felt threatened and in competition with women. now they are where i find my heart. i am comforted and open with women. i am vulnerable and safe with women. these particular women took me into a whole other level of sisterhood though. sacred sharing of hearts and soul. they not only held me but allowed me to hold them. they were vulnerable and let me see them. utter authenticity and openness. when i am at the end of my life i am sure that one of the memories and connections i will recall and think wow it was worth it will be the time i had in peru with these beautiful soul sisters. thank you @mary_brierre @moe_comedy @heavensent2 @janeislistening @caraskitchen @jamievos1 @risingwomanspirit @brandilyn_tebo @krisvangenderen @na.talie8878  @rachelmaefurman and marguerite i love you.

#tribe #women #love #sisterhood #peru #girltrips #lightworker #lifecoach #shadowhunters #shadowwork #sacredsisterhood #aroseylife #aroseylifecoach #life #travel #metoo

text_retweet:
i'm one of those people who literally hand-write things in a journal.  not every day. in fact, there can be months or even years when i don't journal at all. there was one journal i used to write specifically about my late father. i wasn't a parent at the time i started writing in it but i imagined using it one day to tell future offspring or nieces and nephews about their grandfather.

my dad died before instagram, facebook, cell phones with cameras or even frequent use of email. so all my writing was either hand-written in a notebook or saved on an external disc. not an external hard drive but a disc. ha. i kept this particular journal in the drawer of a nightstand by my bed. i can remember exactly when i last looked for it in that drawer. i opened up the drawer and discovered all of the pages - every single one that bore my hand-writing - were ripped out. gone. 
what's worse is when i confronted him about it, he denied it and suggested my daughter had done it. since i knew she hadnâ€™t (given her age, she wasnâ€™t strong enough to break the binding of the hard-covered blank book) i began to wonder if i would have done that. would i have done something like that for some reason and not remembered? i couldn't even believe i was considering such an insane possibility but... i couldn't figure it out. he was so vehement - and convincing - when he said he didn't do it. 
iâ€™ve since learned that getting me to think that i might have done something as preposterous as tear out the pages from my own journal is an example of gaslighting.

my dad died before instagram, facebook, cell phones with cameras or even frequent use of email. so all my writing was either hand-written in a notebook or saved on an external disc. not an external hard drive but a disc. ha. i kept this paicular journal in the drawer of a nightstand by my bed. i can remember exactly when i last looked for it in that drawer. i opened up the drawer and discovered all of the pages - every single one that bore my hand-writing - were ripped out. gone.

text:
@regran_ed from @elishaattai -  as we prepare for awlo 2018 induction and fundraising dinner, please permit me to share a few lines about this global women movement.

african women in leadership organisation (awlo), is for female leaders of african descent, entrepreneurs, professionals, civic leaders - to empower them to be high impact leaders.
we are creating a platform that is empowering and inclusive, for female leaders to sour and
by association garner leadership experience.

our key actions are:

leadership development

we have realized that women leaders must be in a continual process of leadership development to attain their full potential. we provide experiential leadership development opportunities for women.

impact

we believe that making impact is proof of leadership effectiveness. we are sold out to service and also provide opportunities for women leaders to take action or participate in global development.

connecting women

one of our most effective tools for women leadership development has been networking. we provide women opportunities to connect, and develop profitable relationships. our chapters' support-system-framework has been a potent model for this.

for awlo membership registration please  click on this link www.awlo.org/membership

i specially welcome you great women of worth from across the world and all the distinguished #heforshe men to this amazing movement.

website: www.awlo.org

we are not an event but a movement.

thank you! - #regrann

text:
trauma is deeply painful, but that pain can force dramatic, beneficial transformations
________

post traumatic growth (ptg) is a beautiful phenomena, that was discovered in mid 90-s. 
it states that people who go through traumatic experiences experience positive growth overtime. 
________

it can be expressed as: - being psychologically stronger
- being open to new possibilities - having deeper relationships with ppl around you
- enhanced appreciation of life
- increased sense of spirituality
________

ptg is not the same as resilience. being able to bounce back - is a personal attribute.
but founding ways to overcome your challenges and struggles while encountering depression and ptsd - is growth. 
resilient person wonâ€™t be shook to their core by trauma in the first place. others, they would try to understand what had happened to them, and how it recreates the world around them. 
________
interestingly, women show more growth than men, although the difference is not that big.

text:
@kennedywithlove // part 1
.
it was summer. stephanie was 17, had â€œzero experience with boys,â€ and was at a hockey party, wasted, when her best friendâ€™s brother took her to the empty lot next door.
.
when he pinned her up against a fence, she was barely conscious. when he pulled down her pants, she cried. when he pulled out and came on the ground, she couldnâ€™t move. she watched him walk away.
.
it was fall. steph was 21, had just been cheated on again by another boyfriend, and felt worthless, unloveable. in an attempt to feel otherwiseâ€”and feel powerfulâ€”she went on a â€œsexual rampage,â€ sleeping with anyone she could. â€œmy girlfriends and i would go to a bar and drink excessively. iâ€™d see a guy and say, â€˜iâ€™m going to take him home tonight.â€™ that was the goal, the game.â€
.
this went on for two years. until she stumbled upon her future husband, daren, at a saturday night poker party, and feltâ€¦safe.
.
when they wed in 2010, steph was 25. she didnâ€™t knowâ€”and wouldnâ€™t know for another six yearsâ€”that chlamydia, which she had contracted three months before meeting daren, had damaged the cilia on her fallopian tubes, deeming her infertile. (note: she received treatment for the infection, but not in time; her doctor forgot to send in her sti test results.)
.
what she *did* know was the she wasnâ€™t getting pregnant. then, in 2014, she got a call following a pap test: there were pre-cancerous cells in her cervix.
.
it was around this time, when steph was in a â€œreally low spotâ€â€”unhappy in her marriage, her job, her lifeâ€”that she attended a womenâ€™s circle with @jillprescott and â€œcracked right open.â€
.
steph started working with jill one-on-one, and emerged with a â€œdeeper, more spiritual connectionâ€ to herself, a greater capacity to forgive, and a realization: that her experiences gave her a unique ability to help other women in pain.
.
she began facilitating her own womenâ€™s circles, holding energetic space for women to be raw and open and honest. (â€œout of that comes an insane amount of processing and purging of every shitty emotion you can think of.â€)
.
and then: steph got pregnant.
.

text:
i want to talk about rebirth for a moment.
for as long as i can remember, i viewed depression and mood disorders as something permanent; like upon diagnosis, it becomes a death sentence. depression is a condition that once diagnosed, you will live with for the rest of your life. this isnâ€™t up for debate. what is up for debate is whether or not you feed into and fan itâ€™s flames. out of the depths of hell, i have grown the most in my life. a key component of this growth has been the innovation of my state of mind. one of my sexual abusers shares the name of my husband. this name was chanted to me on a regular basis as a child, as a mode of blackmail. the person that knew of and witnessed the abuse was somebody very very close to me, and this person used this name as a means of control, threatening to disclose the abuse to my mother. at seven years old, i always thought it was my fault. i thought i was pregnant. i lived a childhood of complete fear and solitude. iâ€™ll never forget the last time â€œjaredâ€ was uttered to me in the normal menacing fashion, and i looked at this person, and stood my ground while i told my mother everything at age 11.  i was finally free. that was such an incredibly defining moment in my life, and iâ€™ll be honest, when i met my husband, his name kept me frozen in my tracks. i couldnâ€™t fathom utilizing such a terrible name to reference the one i loved; it was actually one of my dating â€˜non-negotiables.â€™ but he showed me day in and day out, that you donâ€™t have to die to be given new life. we all have the opportunity and responsibility to change perspective and stop punishing others as a result of our experiences. iâ€™m elated on the daily that the purest form of unconditional love iâ€™ve ever experienced transformed the pain i lived with for so many years into hope and faith. you too can be given new life, if you put forth the effort... and most importantly, make that conscious choice all on your own.
â€”â€”â€”â€”/////////

@richo_kyle #richardkyle /// this year, un women have set #hearmetoo as the theme of this year's 16 day of activism against gender-based violence. i personally, could not have picked a better theme. 
this year, the #metoo movement have inspired many women to start talking about their sexual violence experience. i am eternally in awe of their bravery and am immensely proud to have been able to witness women rise to become more empowered in these recent years. 
now, i aspire to see more changes in the future regarding the empowerment of women. one way to do it is by putting a stop to gender-based violence. whether we like it or not, as of now women is more prone to experiencing violence in their lifetime.
it is time for that to stop.
.
join me @enambelasffest to contribute in the fight against gender-based violence. /// .

text:
this line from my story (an ongoing rosetta stone, at link in profile), won't go away this morning. i love the intent behind the @ibelieveherireland effort, but i worry sometimes, about the use of memes in this movement (i struggle with shorthand in general, with jargon, hashtags, small things meant to illustrate big thoughts).
.
.
the latest, comparisons of scraps of fabric meant to sketch the vicious disgrace of the trial in cork, in which a teen girl's thong was used as evidence of her supposed consent. â€œclothing is not consent.â€ absolutely. 100%. translation: â€œthe fact that iâ€™m wearing lacy underwear, the fact that my garments are designed to be sexually enticing, no fact of what iâ€™m wearing or not wearing, none of this gives you any rights to my body.â€ .
(let me be clear - i fully support the effort, and my god, if it gives this one survivor, or any survivor, some measure of comfort and solidarity, please keep doing it. i'm not discouraging this offshoot of the movement - quite the opposite.)
.
.
are we making our anger cute, and therefore minimizing it, allowing it to be dismissed?
.
is the shorthand, repeated through self-creation, a manner of getting through, of breaking down concepts that should be simple to begin with, reinforcement through repetition? or is it neutralizing our anger, turning our rage into a photo-app plaything?
.
.
what do you think? .
@thewordforthis

text:
hello, everyone.  my name is richard santiago and iâ€™m contacting you to share a film iâ€™m working on about my good friend, a register nurse, jason b. almeida. jason was a young man who committed suicide after years of workplace bullying.  this film documents his life and heartbreaking death.  we are doing a world-wide premier of this teaser trailer on nov. 21st 2018, to help launch the gofundme page weâ€™ve created to complete this film.  we are also launching a page on our website,  http://www.thebullyexposed.com/jasons-story/, to offer perks for those who donate to help us complete this project.  please share this post and link to all your friends and family.  help us tell jasonâ€™s story.

donâ€™t just share this post one time. please share it every wednesday to honor jasonâ€™s life. keep sharing until the project is funded.

check out these videos to learn more about our project to honor jason:

dear bully pitch video
https://vimeo.com/300931778  dear bully teaser:  the jason bennett almeida story
 https://vimeo.com/300930280

clothes are not consent!!!

text:
during the #16days of activism against gender-based violence, we plan to have a series of conversation on sexual victimization of women and girls in nigeria. we have as guests:

prof chidi odinkalu & miss nana nwachukwu 
mrs iheoma obibi & mr ayo sogunro 
mrs abiodun baiyewu & miss olutimehin adegbeye. 
you're invited to join us. 
kindly follow our twitter handle: @shareanonymousi to participate, ask questions, share your views and our guests would be happy to respond.

in the meantime, tell us what you're doing to fight gender-based violence. use the hashtag #hearmetoo to share with us.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
this painting is dedicated to one of my former best friends in college, who filmed me in the shower, told me he did it to "keep himself from doing something worse," and then tried to blackmail me into not telling anyone. i pressed charges and he got expelled. i'm actually grateful for this experience, because it taught me a lot of valuable lessons that made me a better person without something way more traumatizing having to happen. here's a big fuck you to people who think they can get away with this kind of behavior! â¤ï¸
.
.
.

text:
i'm having trouble sending a text to a couple that offered to help me stabilize. why? i can't find their name on ig in my list of "hearts." i didn't write it down. it didn't occur to me. what about this system isnâ€™t cruel and taxing. really, donâ€™t you just want a world where needs are met with love and joy? #metoo! #heavenhelpus. #iwantanewearthplease. ğŸŒğŸ’šğŸ•Š
blessings. i'm a bit stunned by the question because i've so longed to hear it and yet don't know where it is coming from, karen and bill. 
here's my gut response in three ways: 
1ï¸âƒ£ $300 will give me one week in a hotel with food and small flexibility. 
2ï¸âƒ£ $10,000 will allow me to rent and furnish an apartment as i go about seeking additional funding for a migrating university and decolonial business academy over the coming months. 
3ï¸âƒ£ $500,000 will enable me to truly organize a migrating university and decolonial business academy that runs on entirely transparent accounting practices and is dedicated to helping all people learn how to weather climate chaos and rejuvenate our global ecosystem despite the fascists. that amount will cover three years of funding and the adaptation of a community energy grid -- a power system without fossil fuels -- for free global distribution to my broad network of contacts. 
i don't know you or your personal, ancestral, and economic circumstances. mine are grave. any gift of cash from you to me is one of love. 
to me, love is the most natural currency, and i'll accept any amount that is freely, lovingly, warmly given. i *need* to do this work for regenerative agriculture and prison abolition, and all money will help me push for both. 
with deep bows of gratitude, darshan elena campos.

text:
kesenjangan nilai kontrak aktris perempuan dan laki-laki tidak hanya dialami oleh hollywood. di bollywood pun demikian, dengan rentang jarak nilai yang sangat jauh berbeda antara aktor dan aktrisnya.

namun hal itu tidak dialami olehÂ abhishek bachchanÂ danÂ aishwarya rai. tanpa tedeng aling-aling, abhishek mengungkap bahwa selama ini bayaran yang ia terima kerap kali lebih sedikit daripada nilai kontrak aishwarya rai. "dari sembilan film yang kubintangi bersamanya, delapan di antaranya aishwarya dibayar lebih mahal daripada aku," ujar abhishek seperti dilansir dari pinkvilla.com.

1. ibu abhishek juga dibayar lebih mahal

lebih lanjut, putra bungsu amitabh bachchan dan jaya bachchan ini juga menyebut bahwa ibunya pun dibayar lebih mahal daripada dirinya. meski tidak selalu, namun dalam beberapa kesempatan nilai kontrak jaya bachchan lebih tinggi daripada kontraknya.

abhishek menilai, kesenjangan nilai kontrak yang selama ini jadi perdebatan di india tidak berlaku di keluarganya. ia bisa menerima mengapa aishwarya dibayar lebih mahal, dan mengapa aktris lain juga dibayar lebih mahal daripada dirinya atau ayahnya. "deepika padukone dibayar lebih mahal daripada ayahku di film piku. kalau kamu punya kualitas yang mumpuni, bayaran tinggi akan mengikuti. tapi kalau baru terjun ke dunia film, jangan berharap dapat bayaran sebanyak shahrukh khan," ujarnya.

2. ingin perempuan diperlakukan sama

secara garis besar, abhishek mengungkap bahwa ia ingin semua orang di dunia memperlakukan pria dan wanita dengan setara. sebagai seorang pria yang memiliki kakak perempuan dan seorang anak perempuan, abhishek melihat betapa pentingnya kesetaraan.

kini, ketika india ramai dengan gerakan #metoo, abhishek pun menilainya secara positif. ia berharap dengan banyaknya perempuan yang bersuara dalam gerakan ini, kesetaraan dan keadilan akan segera jadi kenyataan di india. .
.
.
source by : kapanlagi
.
.

text:
part 2:
at some point, i started pushing him away weakly, telling him i didn't want him to touch me like that. he didn't stop immediately. after some more time, he pressed his crotch against my butt, i jumped away and finally managed to tell him i wanted to go home now. that was when he seemed to snap out of it.
he drove me home, telling me how sorry he was, how he would never do it again, asking me of we could just start over. i simply agreed, avoiding to talk as much as possible. when we got to my house, i practically jumped out of the car and ran into my room, barely even greeting my parents. i blocked him on all social media and then lay in my bed to calm down. 
at first, i seemed to suppress how awful i actually felt. my friend i was with texted me (jokingly), asking me what happened, since the guy had told her we kissed. i brushed it off, she seemed to realise something was wrong but didn't push it. they're still friends.
i told another friend just some days after, playing it down a lot as if it didn't bother me, my friend later told me she was confused  how calm i was telling her what happened.
it was days, maybe weeks, after that first that i started breaking down. i talked to that friend again, more serious this time, she comforted me. i told more friends about it since then and talking about it helps, but i just seem to feel worse and worse about what happened. i get mental breakdowns just thinking about it, have nightmares about being raped, i'm incredibly careful making new friends, i avoid meeting the friend i was with because i'm scared to even here about that guy again, and it sickens me. 
i don't know how to talk to my therapist about it, i constantly wonder if it's my fault for not telling him to stop sooner, i could have avoided so much of what happened, but i didn't. i hate myself for feeling so bad about it, since there are so many people that have it so much worse, in the end, he didn't even rape me. i can't get over it. my depression just gets worse. if you have any advice, please, let me know. i really could use it right now.

#metoo #sexualassault #depression #advice

i model in lingerie because iâ€™m full of self love and body positivity, not because i want to be sexualised or raped. what i wear or do does not make me a slut, begging for it, cheap, it is not consent.

text:
hell hath no fury fest 2.0 
@petrol_girls
feminist # post-hardcore from austria, graz and the uk. 
one of the most important #feminist #punk #rock bands of the #metoo era, infusing art and #activism with raging #hardcore. 
both of their albums, talk of violence (released on bomber music) and their most recent release the future is dark (hassle records) are packed full of resonance, #solidarity and the words that all #womxn can relate too. see 'touch me again' (and i will  fucking kill you) https://petrolgirls.bandcamp.com/track/touch-me-again. 
front person ren aldridge not only harbours talent in song writing and performance but also directed and produced the goosebump giving and fist raising video for 'sister' from the future is dark. text:
for those 87 million people probably wondering what was actually done with their data, i went back to christopher wylie, the ex-cambridge analytica employee who blew the whistle on the companyâ€™s problematic operations in the observer. according to wylie, all you need to know is a little bit about data science, a little bit about bored rich women, and a little bit about human psychology.

step one, he says, over the phone as he scrambles to catch a train: - when youâ€™re building an algorithm, you first need to create a training set. that is: no matter what you want to use fancy data science to discover, you first need to gather the old-fashioned way. before you can use facebook likes to predict a personâ€™s psychological profile, you need to get a few hundred thousand people to do a 120-question personality quiz.

the â€œtraining setâ€ refers, then, to that data in its entirety: the facebook likes, the personality tests, and everything else you want to learn from. most important, it needs to contain your â€œfeature setâ€: - the underlying data that you want to make predictions on, wylie says. - in this case, itâ€™s facebook data, but it could be, for example, text, like natural language, or it could be clickstream data â€“ the complete record of your browsing activity on the web. - those are all the features that you want to [use to] predict. at the other end, you need your target variables, the things that youâ€™re trying to predict for. so in this case, personality traits or political orientation, or what have you.

alex hern
the guardian

text:
behind every woman there's a story of survival.
a story of beating the odds, overcoming obstacles and finding a way, the way, while also discovering herself and learning about self-value, and probably while also becoming economically independent and somehow 'looking good' in the process. because the set of conditions somehow expected of us requires also a certain etiquette and  people run the other way if we're being 'bitchy'. and oh, they freak out when we say we're feminists. what's so wrong with asking for equality? with being tired of mistreatment and invisibility? 
mine is a story so peculiar it would take a long time to narrate - a good script. i've been a colombian growing up in a country ravaged by the conflict, i've been a political asylee, i've been a child performer, i've been an american when 9/11 happened and experienced everything positive and negative the us has to offer.  i've left it all and moved to eu.
just like you and her, as a woman i have also experienced sexual violence (multiple times), and discrimination as a minority and as a member of the lgbtq community. the list is long. i've lost loved ones and still grieve and i have been a poet through it all. i love and i dream every day. i'm a proud survivor. a non-apologetic witch. a free human.

and i sure as hell am happy to be here and to fight for my rights. to fight for yours. to stand against fascism, misogyny and discrimination, and i invite you to do the same. no, i expect you to do the same. be our ally. be one of us. (but here's a selfie, for algorithm purposes). #weareallsurvivors #survivorsareeverywhere #metoo #standbyme #fuckfascism #feministsoftheworld #strongwomen #nomakeup #wonderwoman #womenempowerment #womenwhotravel #yotambien #notmypresident #humanrights #tellmeyourstory #westandtogether #itgetsbetter #itmfa #msneverstop #stillnotaskingforit #believesurvivors #believewomen #ibelieveher

text:
please show some love and support to  @julzlovespools !! .

share and read !
.

as many of you know, there were several articles in the news about neal and his sexual abuse. in the espn article, gary ream stated that he was putting neal on leave. ironically, gary ream is one of nealâ€™s close friends and one of the people that tried to intimidate me to keep silent. 
shame on you gary ream! .

gary knew about this abuse long before it was reported to safesport, yet he did nothing. under safesport rules, gary was supposed to report the allegations within 1 day. he never did. instead of putting the interest of young female skateboarders first, gary ream decided to protect his own interest and tried to prevent any bad press that would negatively affect his standing within the olympic movement.  i was told gary ream hired tim curley who was convicted and went to jail for covering up the penn state sexual abuse of young boys by jerry sandusky, is this the guy that will protect the abused or the abuser? 
shame on you gary ream! .

young girls in skateboarding remain susceptible to sexual predators because of people like gary ream, who brush negative press under the rug to protect themselves. garyâ€™s leadership provides protection for sexual predators and promotes the sexual victimization of girls.  neal hendrix shouldnâ€™t be put on leave, he should be put in jail and men like gary ream should be stripped of the power that they failed to exercise.  instead of trying to silence girls who speak up, skateboarding should have leaders that protect all the athletes and give everyone a fair shot. it is people like neal hendrix and gary ream who turn the olympic movement into a toxic environment for women. 
i have taken back my power by exposing these people for who they are. i hope the international olympic committee and its affiliates will demonstrate the courage to exercise their power and safeguard young female athletes by permanently eliminating sexual predators and the men like gary ream who protect them. .

#doyouremember #metoo #metooskateboarding #sexualabusesurvivor
#whyididntreport #iamnotafraidtosayit #imnotafraid #ihavecontrol #sexualassaultisnotok

text:
iâ€™ve received a lot of messages regarding the sexual harassment thatâ€™s ongoing with #missearth so iâ€™m going to take this opportunity to make an official statement.
â€¢
firstly, i would like to say that the team leaders took amazing care of us, when they found out about the actions of cruz they did what they could to protect us from him. they are not in control of his actions, nor did they pass along any private information of the delegates in my group.
â€¢
that being said, cruz is a predator. he approached many of the girls, offered them luxury holidays, trips on his private yacht, nice dinners and expensive handbags. most of us laughed him off because we knew he was a sponsor and we could not be as blunt or rude to him as you would be in a normal situation. he didnâ€™t stop when we told him no. my own personal experience of him was after repeatedly declining his offers and asking to be left alone, he would turn up to my hotel and pester me there. i mentioned the story where me and miss samoa were in the lobby (waiting for one of the staff to bring us an ice cream haha) and cruz turned up. we were both ignoring him and cruz was talking to some of the other girls but then suddenly started shouting â€œengland england come hereâ€, me and miss samoa looked at each other and just ran into the lift to get away from him.
â€¢
we warned everybody in carol productions about him and they said that he would be removed as a sponsor, that he wouldnâ€™t do this again. the real shame is that i have so many fond memories of miss earth and i donâ€™t want to hurt the organisation but there needs to be a lesson here. there are so many men (and women) who abuse their power. cruz has been a sponsor for many years, his money has so far been his bubble, his way of being able to get away with sexual harassment, of avoiding consequences. the shocking thing is he probably doesnâ€™t think heâ€™s in the wrong.
â€¢
but mr cruz, you are.
â€¢
and to every person who sends threatening messages to the girls whoâ€™ve come forward, to those die hard fans who have messaged me telling me they are lying, i beg you to open your eyes. imagine it was your daughter, sister or mother.
â€¢
girls, i stand with you. #metoo

text:
â€˜there is nothing gutsier to me than a person announcing that their story is one that deserves to be told, especially if that person is a woman. as hard as we have worked and as far as we have come, there are still so many forces conspiring to tell women that our concerns are petty, our opinions arenâ€™t needed, that we lack the gravitas necessary for our stories to matter. that personal writing by women is no more than an exercise in vanity and that we should appreciate this new world for women, sit down, and shut up.â€™ .
.
people who know me personally are aware of how besotted i am by memoirs written by women. the above quote by lena dunham in her book 'not that kind of girl' sums up how i feel about women telling their own stories. with the #metoo movement finally gaining momentum at least in urban india, it has never been more important to rally on and support women to share their stories. it is not an indulgence, but an act of empowerment and fortitude. from funny and banal to heartbreaking and traumatic, my natural instinct has always been to veer towards autobiographical writing by women.
.
.
this weekend, i am re-reading radhika vazâ€™s hilarious memoir, unladylike. like all my autographed books, i treat it like a shrine and never lend it to anyone ğŸ˜›
.
.
on that note, what is your favourite non-fiction book by a woman?
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
thanks  @warif_ng >>> what happens to a rape survivor  when she seeks help on the streets?
.
.
abaad, a lebanese ngo, conducted a social experiment to see how bystanders would react.

an actress played the role of a rape survivor seeking help in public. these are the real reactions she got.
blaming the survivor is still very prevalent in our society todayâ€™, it could have happened anywhere and the reactions would still be the same. 
we need to do better as bystanders so that women and girls can live in a society free from rape and sexual violence.  #shameonwho #endsexualviolence #preventsexualassault #supportingsurvivors #metoo  #sdg5 .

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
she takes all strength, bleeds every month.
to nurture the lifeless human growing inside. 
all, over again she puts a veil covering her sadness, widely smiling all the time. 
don't you understand her?
to try to acknowledge the cruelty she faces all day.?
family & children is all her life 
but darling do you know, 
she had bled her clothes, making you feel proud of the tiny boy she gifted you back. 
every morning i see people inside the small temple, 
what made me cry is the fact that she was barred inside for being bleeding on her 40th day.
a little girl,immature of the world, 
lost all respect and reputation that she had earned, 
just a new lady had emerged in her, 
it was the first time that bled, 
so sorry, for her, to be mocked by the class & always called as ' red '.
oh world she's your daughter, 
make sure she's free. 
that's what i pray. .
.
Â©anandarupa_chakrabarti @notes_from__the_diary

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
this afternoon, zimbabwean artist, kresiah mukwazhi leads the conversation on feminist narratives from zimbabwe, materiality and various pertinent social-justice issues highlighted by the artist through her work.
.
inspired by the global #metoo movement, mukwazhi uses her art to shed light on the commonâ€”and yet less publicisedâ€”occurrences of sexual assault in her home country and the rest of southern africa.
.
don't miss this conversation that will unpack her works 'mambokadzi ii' (2018) and 'send me your nudes' (2018) as part of the current exhibition, 'five bhobh - painting at the end of an era'.
.

text:
*trigger warning*
i don't usually make posts like this about my personal life but i have just finished reading this book. statistically, many, many, men and women in my friends list will have been sexually assualted at some point in their lives. whether it was an unwanted touch, or you were violated at gun point, it is still a traumatising and horrible experience, and such acts need to stop. now, i am not writing this to rally an army, but rather to show my solidarity. if anyone reading this has been sexually assaulted and needs someone to talk to, regardless of the circumstances, i am here to listen - judgement free, and confidential. my inbox, texts, snapchat, mailbox, is always open and i will do my upmost to be everything you need a listener to be in your circumstance. i can be the first or last person you tell, but just know i am here for each and every one of you because #metoo

text:
for those 87 million people probably wondering what was actually done with their data, i went back to christopher wylie, the ex-cambridge analytica employee who blew the whistle on the companyâ€™s problematic operations in the observer. according to wylie, all you need to know is a little bit about data science, a little bit about bored rich women, and a little bit about human psychology.

step one, he says, over the phone as he scrambles to catch a train: - when youâ€™re building an algorithm, you first need to create a training set. that is: no matter what you want to use fancy data science to discover, you first need to gather the old-fashioned way. before you can use facebook likes to predict a personâ€™s psychological profile, you need to get a few hundred thousand people to do a 120-question personality quiz.

the â€œtraining setâ€ refers, then, to that data in its entirety: the facebook likes, the personality tests, and everything else you want to learn from. most important, it needs to contain your â€œfeature setâ€: - the underlying data that you want to make predictions on, wylie says. - in this case, itâ€™s facebook data, but it could be, for example, text, like natural language, or it could be clickstream data â€“ the complete record of your browsing activity on the web. - those are all the features that you want to [use to] predict. at the other end, you need your target variables, the things that youâ€™re trying to predict for. so in this case, personality traits or political orientation, or what have you.

alex hern
the guardian

steve bannon left the wh august last year and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit the hijacked party of puppets is obviously just business as usual.

the whole qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that joseph goebbels would have died for. it is obvious that stuff like pizzagateâ„¢ was testing for the 2016 election.

the bigger issue still is that requqlicans are willingly piggybacking this lunacy and abusing the faith of their fellow men while campaigning for the midterms. this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
what happens to a rape survivor  when she seeks help on the streets?
.
.
abaad, a lebanese ngo, conducted a social experiment to see how bystanders would react.

an actress played the role of a rape survivor seeking help in public. these are the real reactions she got.
blaming the survivor is still very prevalent in our society todayâ€™, it could have happened anywhere and the reactions would still be the same. 
we need to do better as bystanders so that women and girls can live in a society free from rape and sexual violence.

today's prompt is:Â what were the most common emotions i experienced during childhood? what did those emotions feel like in my body? what was my behavioral response? would i hide, yell, manipulate, attempt to control my outcome? when we get clear on what experiences created our emotional homeostasis, we can begin the work required to see how these emotional patterns are currently influencingÂ my present behavior and decision-making.

day 3. shewğŸ’¦ learning the chakra system and this is how i see life differently now. if every person on earth recognizes their top three emotions, realizes they are addicted to them, jumps to logic reasoning and acts upon intuition? can you imagine the state of the world we would live in?
.
my top three i experienced in childhood are rage, grief, and anxiety. my body is chemically  addicted to those 3 emotions ~ in that order ~ because they are experienced at a high frequency in childhood. if i daily choose to not use the tools that i have learned in break method, then i actually have an emotional addiction pattern that then serves to influence my daily behavior, choices, actions and labeling of my environment in an effort to bring me back to homeostasis.
pause.
what is this?
â€the emotional state that we experience with the highest frequency in childhood forms.â€
so!
homeostasis is not where i thrive - yet where i survive.
.
rage. i black out. check out. not on planet earth. basically become unrecognizable. words fly out of my mouth that i do not remember saying yet they feel so good saying them at the time! like an addict high. example of this is being triggered by a narcissistic relationship. love bombed for days / weeks and then being ghosted. my addiction cycle then falls into . . .
.
grief. staying in bed. weeping for hours.  not eating. my addiction cycle then falls into . . .
.
anxiety. exercising for hours. no ability to think clearly. super foggy brain. time does not exist. canâ€™t see well perhaps. bills donâ€™t get paid bc of all the above so you get the drift. definitely survival mode.

"i heard he was one of the #anointed ones early on. #princetongraduate and with a cool $300,000 loan from his dad he built #amazon.â€ â€“ lawrence digital
there is so much that i could or couldnâ€™t, not would or wouldnâ€™t, write about that biographical description of #jeffbezos. it touches nearly all of my buttons and trigger warnings. yet i wonâ€™t say more than what that sentence says itself: jeff bezos didnâ€™t make himself, his father did.

yet what about his mother, our mother, this planet?

we are in the midst of the sixth #extinction, and our political and business #leadership is being unmasked. as if it isnâ€™t unhinged from the life that most people lead. and that life, today, is hanging by a thread.

this is my life these days. i sleep on the floor of a friendâ€™s apartment. there is no door between her bedroom, which is actually her apartmentâ€™s living room, and where i sleep. iâ€™m blessed to be here, to feel welcomed, because i have little cash and limited options. i also have far fewer friends and family than i once did.

iâ€™m isolated because most people that i know and love canâ€™t deal with the everyday realities of their lives, much less my life. i move from place to place as often as i can because i fled my home community after a series of hacks and digital attacks that left me terrified and financially impoverished.

and iâ€™m not alone. my story is the #metoo story of this moment.

it is also the story of #amazonstrike, the current campaign of the companyâ€™s warehouse workers who receive pennies on the bitcoin for their labor. bezos, by the way, is now the worldâ€™s richest white man. the list of rich white people is long and storied. it is the history of racism, capitalism, and settler colonialism.

bezos is now world king. off with his head! well, not really.

iâ€™m #peaceful, but iâ€™m #puertorican and pissed off, and i have a phd so iâ€™m going to use my academic intelligence to do whatever i can to draw attention to the emperorâ€™s pants, which are on fire.

speaking of #fire, have you heard of two of the coolest developments in blockchain technology? the first is akoin. the second is #circles.

text:
last night, 16 july 2018, i learned about fetch.ai. over the course of several hours, i read the devteam's white paper on its "emergent intelligence protocol." as i was doing so, i posted a series of comments, stream of consciousness style, to linkedin. because i've been struggling with data security for about four years, and i seem to be the target of hackers of many hats (one of whom could well be the sexual predator technologist in google's employ that i left about four years ago), i practice an emergent strategy of content migration. this article is in keeping with my need for social innovation of this nature.

status update:

i'm still parsing the #data on this news regarding the world's first #ledger built on #blockchain. and by parsing, i'm mean integrating and aggregating this announcement with information related to #treasonsummit. my initial computational formula suggests this: trump & co. are being publicly eliminated. to ensure #transparency and #accountability, the game is live and global, unfolding in real time by any means possible. a gander. a silly goose. just me gaming the system for a giggle because wow, these times are wacky and deeply dangerous.

#metoo #google #deepmind #deepthroat #machinelearning #corporateaccountability

comment 1:

i dig what this team is doing yet pause.... where are the #women, #twospirit, and #genderqueer technologists? smart systems built on and for #selfaware intelligence see gaps and find ways to remedy them. yet how does correction actually happen? we don't know. the internet was first developed for commercial use by the military. insecurity was built into the system. surveillance and warmongering were the goal, not freedom, ecosystem regeneration, and collective liberation. blockchain technology is, i sense, a social corrective, not just a technological development. i'm excited by it. fetch me up. https://www.fetch.ai

comment 2:

i'm now reading the white paper the fetch.ai team wrote. i'm loving it. here's a gem: "the open economic framework (oef) provides life-support for autonomous software agents. these can be thought of as digital entities that are able to make their own decisions. #theylive.

text:
today i made my voice heard. i took part in #slutwalk2018 and joined forces with the magnificent men and women who are fed up with sexual abuse, emotional abuse, physical abuse, slut shaming, and rape.  i was moved by the speakers, and by the love that surrounded us as we marched down swanston street in the middle of melbourne cbd. at one point it came into my mind, shouldn't people know these things? this is common sense and human decency. how did our society get so off track where rape became ok? where lust trumps respect?  where just last week a women's underwear was used in a court evidence claiming the women wanted to be raped due to what she was wearing?... and all of a sudden my body was filled with pride. we are more than survivors, we are warriors, fighting for human decency and respect.  every part of me is glad that i was there today to fight my own demons as well as fight back against this corruption in our society. so let me tell all those who have suffered at the hands of sexual abuse, i believe you. and you are a beautifully amazing human being ..... â¤â¤â¤
.
.
only 17% of reported sexual offences result in a conviction.
.
.
there was a 3.3% increase in the number of sexual assault victims in australia, from 20,025 in 2013 to a five year high of 20,677 in 2014. .
.
persons aged 19 years and under accounted for 60% of all victims of sexual assault;
.
.
@jamespeach1990 thank you so much for joining me today. i dont think i could have done it without a good friend by my side. meant the world to me and you are a beautiful human :) much love to you x
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
[assalamualaikum wr. wb.]
.
tak kenal maka tak sayang. .
disperis adalah kepanjangan dari 'diskusi perempuan islam', sebuah komunitas yang menghimpun perempuan-perempuan  yang berada di wilayah solo dan sekitarnya. komunitas ini  dibentuk sebagai upaya perwujudan ruang mandiri perempuan dalam berdialog dan saling tukar pikiran. .
.
disperis hadir untuk menghimpun perempuan-perempuan  yang peduli dan resah terhadap isu-isu "perempuan", tentu dalam perspektif yang lebih luas dan kompleks. 
untuk kalian perempuan yang peduli 'perempuan' mari berkawan dalam disperis.
banyak kawan, banyak ilmu.
.
insya'allah, disperis akan membuka ruang diskusi pertama dibulan desember mendatang, kata kuncinya adalah
"feminisme?" disana kita akan membahas terkait apa itu feminisme serta mengkajinya dalam world view islam.
insya'allah.
dan untuk kawan2 yang ingin berpartisipasi silakan tinggalkan pesan di kolomkomentar atau dm.

trimakasih .
.
[wassalamu'alaikum wr. wb]

text:
jumping jiminy cricket!

i came home from an evening of spoken word in stl that celebrates black and brown voices of resistance, celebration, and revolution. it was beautiful.

this little cricket, pictured above, was eating the patio plant when i came home.

as i sat there admiring this small animal, a delivery driver arrived to provide food for the neighbors. it took them, the neighbors, at least 15 minutes to arrive. they came in a car and gave zero tip to the delivery driver who's a father and small business owner.

how #rude. and how sad.

lucky us, me and the driver, we had the sweetest exchange while waiting. we spoke of the glorious sunset and the colors of the cricket and its dinner (the cricket was actually the colors of the plant though my hacked #android camera failed to record that). after i said hello in one of the languages he speaks at home, we shifted into talking of the various languages we know and love, even if only a few useful expressions. my contributions were taino, spanish, french, lakota, anishnaabe, cantonese, italian, japanese, if i recall correctly.

we also talked of his young children and our dreams for our community and the world future.

we had the richest exchange in the midst of economic buffoonery on the part of the people who ordered their dinner from a small family business, a mainland chinese restaurant in the heart of turtle island.

main street america* needs to grow up and see the truth that's already here. and here's part of the truth: it isn't just white people who need to open to the winds of change. the family who ordered their dinner and didn't tip the man who came to their doorstep is black.

by the way, do you know the racist history of tipping? it was born after #slavery to ensure that black people, former slaves, never gained a firm economic foundation. #metoo. may we decolonize and regenerate.

we are all existing under systems that muddle our energy, i mean empathy, for people who are outside the borders of our own family, community, nation. we share one global ecosystem, and we can be one love, when we take the teachings of our ancestors to heart.

#migrationisbeautiful

#abolishice

#youarewhatyoueat

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
i am all for women expressing themselves however they want (unless itâ€™s harmful to a marginalized group). what troubles me about #metoo is the expectation that women who have been hurt or traumatized should share their stories. i thought about doing that and i wrote a draft. then i realized, i do not want to share this publicly. i also bought a shirt that has #metoo on it. i canâ€™t wear it. i feel like iâ€™m advertising my very private trauma. 
hereâ€™s what bugs me the most, though. womenâ€™s pain is so public already. in the news. on tv. in movies. in music. in graphic novels. in video games. in pornography. itâ€™s an integral part of our culture. men as perpetrators are practically invisible. we are either repulsed or entertained by a womanâ€™s pain, but we donâ€™t seem to react as strongly to the men who cause that pain. and in real life , we often see and hear victims/survivors, but we rarely see the men who hurt them. women have to keep quiet or there will be consequences. so many abusers and rapists get to be anonymous.

i would like to see a #himtoo movement where abusive, rapist men are called out and publicly shamed while their victims get to remain anonymous. we need to transfer the shame and ostracism women feel to the men who perpetuate violence against them. 
#metoo #himtoo

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
this is not something i'd usually post. this type of writing i keep to myself. why show people what i've gone through as i've been told many times these are things you keep to yourself. well, screw that. screw silence. screw suffering alone. there are somethings i will never comprehend. things i don't talk about. heavy things inside of me that keeps me apart from everyone else. here is something honest for you.

text:
decolonial bizness world is a free and open method for business education that promotes reparations and decolonization. 
#reparations means repairing the damage that racism, capitalism, and settler colonialism have produced globally through formal, economic amends. #decolonization means creating open pathways for life to thrive on this planet as we move into the new sun. both reparations and decolonization involve abolishing borders and prisons and restoring the #sacred connections between humans and the many other forms of life that live on this planet, earth, as we face #climatechaos, the #sixthextinction, and #proudfascism.
#decolonialbiznessworld is made for the magicians of the global economy, those of us who have been #forced to the margins of capitalist accumulation, while serving its masters and everyday beneficiaries. we have been made marginal even as we remain #theglobalmajority. decolonial bizness world is also made for our allies, for people who see #truth through #delusion and #violence and are willing to put their money where their #mantra lives: on the books and into daily sacred #practice.
this article focuses on calculating for reparations, looking at the costs of #policeviolence from multiple perspectives. may we all have healing justice and #endpoliceterrorism.
in this video, i provide a verbal description of the method, which is what adrienne maree brown calls an #emergentstrategy. this particular video draws attention to the lives of two people who were recently murdered by police. their families and #beloved communities miss them. may we #honor and #uplift the people who survive them, including you and #metoo.

it usually takes me about 15 tries before i can teach the method with greatest ease and spoken eloquence. i'll be doing a series of videos on reparations focusing on these two cases because, to me, they speak to the horrors of this time as well as the various beautiful possibilities we have for global transformation. each video will show the further development of this free and open method for calculating reparations and showcase some of the ways i deploy justice.

text:
part of #healing and moving through feelings of #guilt and #shame is finding allies, people who #inspire and remind you of your #beauty and divine #nature. healing is the heart of the many global movements for #reparations and #decolonization.

healing is the polar opposite of what most of the world's political and business leadership seek to sell. hence the title of this article, which speaks to my own sorry experiences over the last four years.

text:
have you ever watched this video, "man down" by #rihanna, the founder of #fenty who was also named harvard's #philanthropist of the year in 2017 and just turned down performing at the #superbowl to show solidarity with #blacklivesmatter as a global movement and #colinkaepernick as a sacred vision on and off the field?

try it now.

here's what i sense as i watch the video, its words and story. the woman in the video, rihanna, recounts how she came to murder a man in public. she was raped. the rape isn't shown. it is alluded to through direct cuts between a man holding her mouth as he presses her against a wall and she struggles. cut. her body slides down the wall as she crumples, literally, to the earth.

now, if you know the #statistics for intimate violence such as #rape, #incest, and #assault, you know how common it is. if you're a #survivor, you also know that a rape, for example, doesn't just happen once. it happens in flashes of memory all the time if you have yet to heal or are denied healing. #metoo. #timesup. #kavanope. #insurance.

part of what is so beautiful about this video, which is haunting in its honesty, is that it also showcases how #trauma expands its #socialimpact. #financialmarkets. #financeandeconomy.

now, if you know the statistics for women who have been incarcerated, you know that an overwhelming number of them are there for protecting themselves against their abusers. you also know that women survivors are the most vulnerable after leaving their abusers. and you know that men who murder the women who leave receive far lighter sentences than their female or trans counterparts. #prisonabolition. #metoomvmt. #accounting.

as many of you know, there were several articles in the news about neal and his sexual abuse. in the espn article, gary ream stated that he was putting neal on leave. ironically, gary ream is one of nealâ€™s close friends and one of the people that tried to intimidate me to keep silent. 
shame on you gary ream! 
gary knew about this abuse long before it was reported to safesport, yet he did nothing. under safesport rules, gary was supposed to report the allegations within 1 day. he never did. instead of putting the interest of young female skateboarders first, gary ream decided to protect his own interest and tried to prevent any bad press that would negatively affect his standing within the olympic movement.  i was told gary ream hired tim curley who was convicted and went to jail for covering up the penn state sexual abuse of young boys by jerry sandusky, is this the guy that will protect the abused or the abuser? 
shame on you gary ream! 
young girls in skateboarding remain susceptible to sexual predators because of people like gary ream, who brush negative press under the rug to protect themselves. garyâ€™s leadership provides protection for sexual predators and promotes the sexual victimization of girls.  neal hendrix shouldnâ€™t be put on leave, he should be put in jail and men like gary ream should be stripped of the power that they failed to exercise.  instead of trying to silence girls who speak up, skateboarding should have leaders that protect all the athletes and give everyone a fair shot. it is people like neal hendrix and gary ream who turn the olympic movement into a toxic environment for women. 
i have taken back my power by exposing these people for who they are. i hope the international olympic committee and its affiliates will demonstrate the courage to exercise their power and safeguard young female athletes by permanently eliminating sexual predators and the men like gary ream who protect them. #metoo #metooska

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think itâ€™s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people donâ€™t necessarily know itâ€™s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so itâ€™s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that youâ€™re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of peopleâ€™s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldnâ€™t have seen, and couldnâ€™t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, â€œwould work for anyoneâ€. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean theyâ€™re mercenaries. theyâ€™ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

itâ€™s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing â€“ at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public â€“ our intimate family connections, our â€œlikesâ€, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole thatâ€™s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

text: movie #68 of 2018: fantastic beasts: the crimes of grindelwald. letâ€™s cut to the chase â€“ queenie is a horrible and crazy person. everyone should agree on that. from the moment she appears in this film sheâ€™s being terrible. jacob is the wizarding world equivalent of #metoo as he is being forced into an agreement under duress and has most likely been sexually assaulted as well. itâ€™s played for a joke, but itâ€™s off putting when you really stop and think about it. overall though this is a better movie than the first one with some great moments in it, but itâ€™s undermined by a meandering plot and a couple of characters that should have been on the cutting room floor. in one scene we are told two different stories of the same event only to then be told a third version, and either one of those is true, or the future films will make none of them be. itâ€™s frustrating and quite pointless and left me scratching my head. jacobâ€™s sacrifice in the previous movie is rendered moot here. that ending to the last movie should never have happened, or jacob (a great character) should not have been in this one. or, if he was, make half the movie trying to figure out how to get his memory back. somehow everyone loves newt â€“ leta, tina, and his assistance. which that was a great scene. iâ€™m shocked they put an overtly yet symbolic, um, sexual fantasy scene in there with her telling him to take his shirt off and then she got drenchedâ€¦ bold for a movie like this! depp and law are outstanding as is most everyone else. the fantastic beasts themselves are far more fun here than the previous movie, and the more films in the wizarding world that come out from potter to these, the more i realize i donâ€™tâ€™ always like the stories so much as the world itself. itâ€™s worth seeing and quite fun but there are a ton of issues in it. but check it out! text:
"panty portrait: beaver" from the panty project, 8 of 51
.

fiber art, archival pigment print on museum cotton rag, 19 x 14 inches .
the panty project is an ongoing social practice project. participants, womxn and those who identify as womxn, courageously share with me their stories of experienced gendered transgressions and violent aggressions, whether cultural and/or interpersonal. participants write a word or phrase onto the panel of their selected undergarment; i hand-embroider over their mark-making and photograph them as if they have been taken off. this work addresses the inherent misogyny within our language, and the consequential "essestializing" of womxn, which reduces womxn, and those who identify as womxn, to "less than." this work is about healing and transcendence. 
womxn's long-silenced voices must be heard.
.

text:
the tears we cried election night 2016
the insults
the trump apologists
the misogyny
the racism
the bigotry
the kids in cages
the "lock her ups"
the double standards
the sexual harassment
the "fair and balanced" media
the treatment of hillary
the treatment of our daughters, our sisters, our mothers, ourselves
all this and more has lead us to this moment.
it is not enough
it is only a beginning 
but our voices will be heard.

enjoy the moment ladies. let's make trouble!

text:
@richo_kyle our volunteer ambassador /// this year, un women have set #hearmetoo as the theme of this year's 16 day of activism against gender-based violence. i personally, could not have picked a better theme. 
this year, the #metoo movement have inspired many women to start talking about their sexual violence experience. i am eternally in awe of their bravery and am immensely proud to have been able to witness women rise to become more empowered in these recent years. 
now, i aspire to see more changes in the future regarding the empowerment of women. one way to do it is by putting a stop to gender-based violence. whether we like it or not, as of now women is more prone to experiencing violence in their lifetime.
it is time for that to stop.
.
join me @enambelasffest to contribute in the fight against gender-based violence. /// .

text: photo by @sathuman | after the #metoo movement began calling out sexual misconduct by people in power, these dallas twins decided to speak out about their alleged abuse under father czeslaw â€œchesterâ€ domaszewicz in the catholic church. the experiences the women say they endured which include sexual harassment, groping and suggestive comments resulted in a â€œcrippledâ€ belief in organized religion for at least one of them. myrna and micaela dartsonâ€™s alleged abuse at st. peter the apostle catholic church â€“ and even in their own house â€“ dissolved their longtime spiritual home into a place of fear and disgust. father domaszewicz has been a priest with the diocese of venice in southwest florida since 1991. after we began asking the diocese questions in october about the dartson case, the dallas office notified local police of the case and the venice diocese put domaszewicz on administrative leave. read more about their case at the link in our bio.
